{
  "texts": [
    "In order to better serve the processing of agricultural products, future harvesting equipment should focus on simplicity, high precision, high automation, and low cost.",
    "For example, it is possible to combine the harvesting process with the grading and transport of fruits to reduce the costs required for segmented harvesting.",
    "The lower recognition efficiency of vision systems used for fruit picking can affect the accuracy of fruit picking (Wan and Goudos 2020).",
    "In addition, the recognition efficiency of picking equipment can be reduced by a variety of external factors, including the complexity of the fruit-growing environment, such as whether the fruit is obscured by debris, branches, or overlapping growth (Xiao et al. 2023; Karkee et al. 2018).",
    "Natural conditions, such as the light, color, shape, texture of the fruit, inclement weather, noise, and geography, can also negatively affect the recognition efficiency, making it difficult for the visual recognition system to accurately identify the location of the fruit, and these problems seriously affect the picking efficiency (Tang et al. 2020a, b; Liu et al. 2020)."
  ]
}